channel.title: Taking 1 model request before I leave this for good
channel.description: Some of you may know me from way back when, when I was a subtly bright model maker. Since then I have moved on with my life, got a job, got into other things, and will actually be getting married soon. I've decided to leave with a small gift to the community though, maybe a chance at retribution to keep my name living in these forums? I don't know.. Anyways.. This is a community effort. I would like you to either submit a model request, or vote. The model request with most votes will be made by yours truly. I hope to see some unique ideas from you guys. Peace.

item.title: Taking 1 model request before I leave this for good
item.dc:creator: @CoonHunter CoonHunter
item.description:
@CoonHunter wrote:

[quote=“dylan_0789, post:19, topic:403076”][quote author=CoonHunter link=topic=500138.msg3660375#msg3660375 date=1310329493]

Think I might do your ak, coon, if linky doesn’t have a go at it.

When my permit app gets approved im going to look at buying one. If you want i’ll send pics if different angles. That is, if it gets approved.

Like every other American, I see

Not many 19 year.old Americans can say they own 5 vehicles though. If I get that gun (turns out dont need permit unless I wanna make it full auto) i’ll prolly be tge only person in Mississippi to own it. Yes i’m an American, but hey, nobody said i’m getting it to kill people with. I just want a nice ‘toy’
[/quote]
Exactly, every other American. You think the stereotype is that you go around killing people? No, its that there is a huge population that, as soon as they’re given the legal right to, will go out and buy a gun to have one(a “toy” as you call it). I personally have no problem with that, I just thought it would be funny to point out the stereotype

@ the (totally unrelated) five car comment, I as well could get 5 cars, its just $3300 a year on insuring one is enough. Fuck insurance companies. I would assume you don’t have em all insured, right? Because if insurance in the States is like it is in lower mainland BC, you’d be whoring yourself out to pay the 5 cars insurance payments off

So if any of you think I’m bashing Americans, leave.[/quote]
Actually currently only 1 is uninsured because I need to get a set of blinkers first, as well as an inspection sticker. Currently the set of blinkers I am going to get are going to cost around $150 or so. Anyways, for 4 vehicles (2 have full coverage (one has roadside), others are be liability) I currently pay around $900 or so every 6 months.
